I, ‘look at it once; why, the end of it—the foot part—what a small sort 
of end it is; whereas, if a broad footed farmer kicked me, there’s a devilish 
broad insult. But this insult is whittled down to a point only.’ But now 
comes the greatest joke of the dream, Flask. While I was battering away at the 
pyramid, a sort of badger-haired old merman, with a hump on his back, takes me 
